            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>HubSpot data shows businesses publishing 16+ posts per month get 3.5x more traffic than those publishing 0-4. But consistency matters more than volume \u2014 4 well-optimized posts monthly beats 20 rushed ones.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Do blog posts still work for SEO in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Blog posts remain the highest-leverage format for informational and long-tail keywords, and now anchor Answer Engine Optimization by feeding LLMs the structured, entity-rich content they cite. AI Overview traffic has amplified their value.</p></div></div>
